rComments: This guy is the worst professor I have ever encountered. He not only doesn't care about his students, but he actively acts in their worst interests. Avoid at all costs. Not only will you learn nothing, but he may break your will to continue in the field.

This is the worst professor I had for the 4 year undergraduate experience. He seems to be smart person, but he is just not a helpful person. He even alleges something about certain student just based on his assumption, and he even deducts final marks based on his allegation without solid proof.

He is very smart, but it's gotten to his head. He is an arrogant ass with a superiority complex who will go out of his way to make some subversive comment to undermine your intelligence.  His general attitude is that he can't be bothered by people with mortal brains, and doesn't take criticism well.
I am very dissapointed that U of T has a professor such as him. He seems very smart, but he is the most unhelpful professor I've had until now.
